race.comment: FEDERAL NOTICE (6) has a strong record here with two wins and three placings from five starts. Comes off a (18.13) win last time, scoring by 4.5 lengths in a Grade 4/5 over 320m at this track. Looks suited and should go close. SHY SHEENA (1) showed good early burn and was there until turning but swamped late to finish 6th at this track in Grade 5 company. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can do much better this time. ANJO TOPAZ (5) could finish only among the minors last time (18.42) at this track, bringing a three run winning streak to an end. Super consistent and can feature with the right run. JET'S DIGGER (7) racing over this course and distance brings the best out in him.
